
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-sdecugis-dime-diameter-erp-01.txt'>
    <title>"Diameter support for EAP Re-authentication Protocol (ERP)", Sebastien Decugis</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-sdecugis-dime-diameter-erp-01.txt</link>
    <description>The EAP Re-authentication Protocol (ERP) provides a mechanism to optimize EAP authentication delay in the case of re-authentication, which can be significant in roaming mobile situation.  This mechanism assumes that a protocol for Authentication, Authorization and Accounting (AAA) is available to transport ERP between the authenticator(s) and the EAP/ERP server. draft-gaonkar-radext-erp-attrs-03 specifies the transport of ERP using RADIUS.  This document specifies the transport of ERP using Diameter.</description>
    <dc:date>2009-06-06T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
